{
  "stem": "9168.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The purpose was to manufacture a typhus convalescent serum.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And infection was accomplished by laceration of the skin, and the introduction of a typhus virus by contagious lice or by the intravenous or intramuscular injection of fresh blood containing the typhus virus.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now to maintain a constant source of fresh infected blood, three to five inmates per month were artificially infected to provide the blood when it was needed.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And substantially, all of these people died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in Denver we have a survivor who told me that of 50 people in his block who were selected for this experiment, 17 survived.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he was one of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The 11th experiment was poison, conducted from 1943 to '44 at Buchenwald and Sachsenhausen to investigate the effect of poison on humans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now some of these 12 experiments had absolutely no scientific objective to heal or cure, but rather to kill or exterminate.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was one of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Poison bullets were shot into Russian prisoners of war, not to test an antidote for poison but to determine how fast death occurred, taking up to two hours and nine minutes.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Poison was also secretly administered in food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the doctors stood behind curtains to watch the reactions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "All died, or were deliberately killed, to permit autopsies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The photographs and anthropological measurements were taken of these selected victims.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they were killed and defleshed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Military Tribunal One was established on October 25, 1946, to hear this medical case, concluded in July 1947.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Seven doctors, including Karl Brandt, were sentenced to death by hanging, five sentenced to life imprisonment, two sentenced to 20 years-- one to 15 years and one to 10 years-- and seven were found not guilty and released.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
